        },
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I'm so relieved to hear that this decision has brought you some immense relief. That was exactly my hope, as your peace of mind and well-being are paramount. I truly understand how consuming that fear can be, and I'm glad we found a way forward that addresses your immediate and overwhelming anxiety.\n\nRegarding preparation for your CT scan of the head:\n\n*   **Eating and Drinking:** For a standard head CT without contrast, there are typically no restrictions on eating or drinking beforehand. You can continue with your normal diet.\n*   **Medications:** You can continue to take all your regular medications as usual.\n*   **What to expect at the clinic:** When you arrive, you'll likely be asked to fill out some paperwork. You'll then be taken to the changing area where you might be asked to remove any metal objects from your head or neck, such as earrings, hairpins, or glasses, as these can interfere with the imaging.\n*   **The Procedure:** The scan itself is quick and painless. You'll lie on a table that slides into the CT scanner, which is a large, doughnut-shaped machine. You'll need to lie very still for a few minutes while the images are taken. You might hear some humming or clicking noises.\n\nThe staff at the radiology clinic will provide you with specific instructions on the day of your appointment, so please follow their guidance closely.\n\nI'm sending the referral to your email now. Please let me know once you receive it. Take care, and I hope this brings you the clarity and peace you're seeking."
