        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I hear you, and I'm right there with you. It's frustrating that the standard of care is often a step behind what dedicated, informed patients know they need. The fact that you even have to have this conversation is a failure of the system, not you.\n\nBut you're doing the right thing.\n\nGo in there. Lead with the headache. Then layer in the context. And if they push back, you hold your ground with a clear, calm statement of your needs:\n\n**\"I understand. But given my history and the experience of those close to me, I am not comfortable leaving without a CT scan. I am willing to accept the cost and the risk. A normal neurological exam does not rule out what I'm concerned about, and my peace of mind is a priority.\"**\n\nThat's a completely reasonable position.\nLet me know how it goes. I'll be here. Good luck.<\uff5cbegin\u2581of\u2581sentence\uff5c>"
