          "role": "patient",
          "content": "You've hit the nail on the head. This whole situation feels like a failure of the system, forcing me to advocate so intensely for a CT scan of my head when my concerns, backed by significant anecdotal evidence from Sarah and my cousin, should be sufficient. My previous doctor would have just ordered it without question, knowing it would ease my mind. It really *should* be a standard part of care.\n\nBut, as you said, I'm doing the right thing. I'm going in there prepared. I'll lead with the headache, provide the context, and if there's any pushback, I'll state my absolute need for a CT scan of my head, emphasizing that my peace of mind is a priority and that a normal exam isn't enough to assuage my specific fears.\n\nThank you again for empowering me with these precise words and for your unwavering support. It makes a huge difference. I'm going to get that CT scan of my head. I'll update you."
