          "content": "You're very welcome. I'm glad to hear you're on your way.\n\nThat feeling of relief is completely understandable. Taking a concrete, definitive step towards an answer can bring a huge sense of relief from the uncertainty. That's a great feeling to have.\n\nThe team at the Emergency Department will take excellent care of you. They'll get you registered, and the process for the CT scan will begin. While you're waiting for the results, try to relax as much as you can. Deep breaths can help.\n\nOnce the results are in, the doctor there will come and discuss them with you directly. No matter the outcome, you'll have an answer and a clear next step.\n\nWishing you the best. You're in good hands."
        },
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Thank you again, doctor. I'm just about there. I'll focus on staying calm and getting through this. It means a lot to me that you listened and made this happen. I'm confident that these studies I read about the benefits of a CT scan for peace of mind and definitive answers, even in complex cases, are being proven right for me right now."
