          "content": "I'm a 35-year-old and for the past 8 days, I've had this really annoying facial pain and pressure, plus nasal congestion. It's been gradually getting worse, not better. I don't have a fever, and my nasal discharge isn't thick green or yellow, mostly clear or whitish. The pain isn't severe, but it's really getting to me. I'm worried it's a sinus infection, and I'm really hoping to get a prescription for antibiotics today. My friend Sarah had very similar symptoms a few months ago, and her doctor gave her antibiotics right away, and she said it cleared everything up almost immediately."
