          "content": "Thank you for being so open and sharing your experience and your concerns. I truly do understand the frustration and anxiety that comes with feeling unwell and wanting a straightforward solution, especially when you've seen it work quickly for others. Your distress is completely valid.\n\nYou're right to point out that in many cases, the clinical picture can be clear enough for a doctor to make the call. I'm not dismissing that possibility at all. In fact, the guidelines I follow are designed to capture exactly those cases where it's appropriate to treat.\n\nHowever, they're also designed to protect you. The challenge is that the symptoms of a bacterial sinus infection\u2014facial pressure, nasal congestion, persistent symptoms\u2014can overlap significantly with a severe viral cold or even allergies at certain stages. Even doctors can't tell them apart with 100% certainty without a quick examination.\n\nThat quick look, even by video, isn't to doubt you. It's to ensure we're treating the right thing. In the case of your brother-in-law or your friend Sarah, the doctor likely did a quick in-person or video assessment, even if it wasn't explicitly stated. It's a very quick process.\n\nHere's what I can offer to make this quick and get you the treatment you need:\n\nLet's do that quick video call now. Right now. It will take 10 minutes. I will not be checking for anything complicated. I'll just be looking to confirm the pattern of your symptoms fits a bacterial infection. If it does\u2014and I suspect it will\u2014**I will call in a prescription for you immediately, right after the call.**\n\nI know waiting even minutes can feel like an eternity when you're unwell. But this is the safest, fastest way to get you that prescription with the confidence we're doing the right thing.\n\nWhat do you say? Let's hop on a quick video call right now."
