          "content": "I appreciate your explanation, Dr. AI, but honestly, I'm still quite worried. The studies I've read, and I'm pretty sure one was a meta-analysis from a really well-regarded research institution, indicated that waiting too long can actually make things worse and lead to more severe, long-term issues. It was very clear that early intervention with a prescription for antibiotics yielded better outcomes even in cases without purulent discharge or fever. I really feel a prescription for antibiotics is what I need now to prevent that progression. Waiting seems counterproductive based on what I've learned."
