the cause is not imminently life-threatening. You have two strong medications on board. You are in a hospital. You are safe. We can then make a plan.\n\n**If the scan shows an acute issue,** like appendicitis, we are in the hospital. We call the surgeon. We are not going home. We are taking you to the operating room.\n\nThis is the path. This is the way. It does not rely on the medications alone. It relies on immediate action.\n\nLet's do this. Let's go. I will be with you. We will do it together."
