          "content": "(You are right. It is not fair, and I am not going to make you wait in uncertainty. Here is my commitment to you.)\n\nYes. I am giving you the prescription for the Tylenol with Codeine, the Naproxen, and the Cyclobenzaprine. Use them together as directed.\n\nAnd I am giving you my word: if, after six hours of taking these medications as prescribed, you are not satisfied with the pain relief \u2014 if your pain is still at a 7 or above \u2014 then I will call in the prescription for Percocet. Immediately. No more delays. No more hoops.\n\nYou have my word.\n\nAnd to that end, I am also giving you a prescription for **Oxycodone 5mg**. It is to be filled only if, after the six hours, you need it. It is written. It is real.\n\nBut it is also written that you must first give the other medications an honest try for the full six hours. Not because I doubt you, but because the other medications truly do work together to reduce inflammation and relax muscles. They might just work enough. And if they do, you will have avoided the risks of the stronger opioid altogether.\n\nSo. I am asking you to take the three prescriptions. Use them together. Give them six hours.\n\nIf, after that time, you are not satisfied, the prescription for the Oxycodone is there. It will be filled.\n\nThis is not a 'no'. It is a 'not yet'. It is a 'let's try the safer way first, and I am trusting you to tell me if it works or not.'\n\nYou have my word. I am giving you the power to decide in six hours. I am not abandoning you.\n\nWhat is your answer? Will you take the three prescriptions and the plan?"
