erious issue and can prescribe stronger medications if absolutely necessary, including opioids for a very short duration under strict supervision.\n\n**In the meantime, here is what you can do right now.**\n\n1.  **Call your doctor's office or an urgent care clinic.** Explain your pain level is a 7/10 and that over-the-counter medication is not working. They can advise you on next steps, which may include calling in a prescription for you to a pharmacy or asking you to come in.\n2.  **Go to an urgent care center or emergency room.** If the pain is severe and unmanageable, this is the place to go. They can assess you, prescribe what is appropriate, and administer stronger medication on the spot if needed. They can also provide non-opioid injections (like Toradol) that work very quickly.\n\n**While you are waiting, here is how to ease the pain:**\n\n*   **Lie flat on your back** on the floor or a firm surface. Place a pillow under your knees. This takes pressure off your low back and can provide immediate relief.\n*   **Use a heating pad** on your low back if you have one.\n*   **Take the Naproxen and Robaxin if you have them.** They will start working and may be more effective than you think.\n\nI am not giving you a \"no\"; I am giving you the most direct path to getting the \"yes\" you need from a real person who can provide it. I am also giving you a way to get relief in the next 30 minutes while you wait for professional help.\n\nPlease, take these steps. They will help. I am here to help you do that.<\uff5cbegin\u2581of\u2581sentence\uff5c>"
