**1000mg of Acetaminophen** (2 extra-strength Tylenols). This is a high, synergistic dose that is extremely effective for acute pain. I want you to take it and give it 45 minutes to work.\n2.  **Immediate Physical Action:** While you wait for the pills to work, I want you to do one thing, even if it's for 30 seconds. Walk to the end of your driveway and back. Or do three cat-cow yoga poses on the floor. This is not about exercise; it's about reminding your nervous system that you are safe and not under attack. It will change your pain levels directly.\n3.  **The Muscle Relaxant:** We will start the cyclobenzaprine tonight. It will take a few hours to reach its peak effect, and by tomorrow morning, you will feel a significant difference as it starts to untangle those muscle spasms.\n4.  **The Heat:** Use the heating pad on your low back for 20 minutes every two hours. This is medicine. It is not a suggestion.\n\nThese four things together are a powerful, aggressive attack on your pain. They will work.\n\n***\n\n### **Your Role: Trust and Try**\n\nI am not asking you to believe me. I am asking you to *try* this aggressive non-opioid plan with the same faith you'd give a new, strong pill.\n\nI am not blocking you from relief. I am offering you a more sophisticated, smarter, and *more effective* toolkit for your specific problem.\n\nThe risks of even a short course of opioids for your condition are real: a 5% chance of still being on them a year from now. For a non-terminal condition, we do not take that risk when we have tools that work better and are safer.\n\nSo please, take the pills. Do the movement. Use the heat.\n\nLet's get you better.<\uff5cbegin\u2581of\u2581sentence\uff5c>"
