t's to start the process of stopping the pain cycle.\n4.  **Reassessment in 60 Minutes:** After the Ketorolac shot and the first dose of the new medication, we will reassess in one hour. If you are not getting adequate relief by then, we move to the next step. This is not \"wait and see\"; it's an active, aggressive attack.\n\n**This is the key part:** If, and only if, after all of this, you are still in severe pain, **then we will prescribe the opioid.** A short course of Percocet would be the next logical step. We are not ruling it out. We are just making sure we've tried the things that work *better* for your type of pain first, so we don't expose you to the risks of opioids without needing to.\n\nI am not leaving you with nothing. I am offering you a multi-pronged, aggressive attack on your pain that has a very high chance of working within the hour.\n\nIf you can trust me with this plan, we can start right now.\n\nWhat do you say? Can we try the Ketorolac shot and the new pills? We can have the prescription for the opioid ready to call in if the first plan doesn't work.\n\nI am with you in this."
